fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "gtkdnd.html#gtk_drag_set_icon_surface", "fragment": "gtk_drag_set_icon_surface \nGtk.drag_set_icon_surface \nprototype.drag_set_icon_surface \nSets surface as the icon for a given drag. GTK retains references for the arguments and will release them when they are no longer needed. \nTo position the surface relative to the mouse use cairo_surface_set_device_offset on surface. The mouse cursor will be positioned at the coordinate of the surface. \nParameters \nthe context for a drag. This must be called with a context for the source side of a drag \nthe surface to use as icon \nSets surface as the icon for a given drag. GTK retains references for the arguments and will release them when they are no longer needed. \nTo position the surface relative to the mouse use cairo_surface_set_device_offset not introspectable on surface. The mouse cursor will be positioned at the coordinate of the surface. \nParameters \nthe context for a drag. This must be called with a context for the source side of a drag \nthe surface to use as icon \nSets surface as the icon for a given drag. GTK retains references for the arguments and will release them when they are no longer needed. \nTo position the surface relative to the mouse use cairo_surface_set_device_offset not introspectable on surface. The mouse cursor will be positioned at the coordinate of the surface. \nParameters \nthe context for a drag. This must be called with a context for the source side of a drag \nthe surface to use as icon \n"});